{"_id": "21843334|None", "id": "21843334", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Infect. Agents Cancer; 2011 Aug 15; 613. doi:10.1186/1750-9378-6-13", "year": "2011", "article-id_pmc": "PMC3170208", "type": "title", "authors": "Di Vuolo V, Buonaguro L, Izzo F, Losito S, Botti G, Buonaguro FM, Tornesello ML", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "TP53 and MDM2 gene polymorphisms and risk of hepatocellular carcinoma among Italian patients.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "7157", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "460"}, "text": "TP53", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "4193", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "1793"}, "text": "MDM2", "locations": [{"offset": 9, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006528", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "hepatocellular carcinoma", "locations": [{"offset": 45, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 84, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 94, "text": "BACKGROUND: Single-nucleotide polymorphisms within TP53 gene (codon 72 exon 4, rs1042522, encoding either arginine or proline) and MDM2 promoter (SNP309; rs2279744), have been independently associated with increased risk of several cancer types. Few studies have analysed the role of these polymorphisms in the development of hepatocellular carcinoma. METHODS: Genotype distribution of TP53 codon 72 and MDM2 SNP309 in 61 viral hepatitis-related hepatocellular carcinoma cases and 122 blood samples (healthy controls) from Italian subjects were determined by PCR and restriction fragment length polymorphism (RFLP). RESULTS: Frequencies of TP53 codon 72 alleles were not significantly different between cases and controls. A significant increase of MDM2 SNP309 G/G and T/G genotypes were observed among hepatocellular carcinoma cases (Odds Ratio, OR = 3.56, 95% Confidence Limits, 95% CI = 1.3-9.7; and OR = 2.82, 95% CI = 1.3-6.4, respectively). CONCLUSIONS: These results highlight a significant role of MDM2 SNP309 G allele as a susceptibility gene for the development of viral hepatitis-related hepatocellular carcinoma among Italian subjects.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "7157", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "460"}, "text": "TP53", "locations": [{"offset": 145, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "rs1042522", "type": "Mutation", "subtype": "SNP"}, "text": "rs1042522", "locations": [{"offset": 173, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001120", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "arginine", "locations": [{"offset": 200, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D011392", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "proline", "locations": [{"offset": 212, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "4193", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "1793"}, "text": "MDM2", "locations": [{"offset": 225, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "rs2279744", "type": "Mutation", "subtype": "SNP"}, "text": "rs2279744", "locations": [{"offset": 248, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 326, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006528", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "hepatocellular carcinoma", "locations": [{"offset": 420, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "7157", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "460"}, "text": "TP53", "locations": [{"offset": 480, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "4193", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "1793"}, "text": "MDM2", "locations": [{"offset": 498, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D006525", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "viral hepatitis", "locations": [{"offset": 516, "length": 15}]}